Several districts face high risk, and nearly two million people could be affected by the unexpected, renewed monsoon downpours.
title: Eastern Nepal hit by Monsoon: At least 22 dead in landslides, flood

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Former Cisco CEO John Chambers warns AI will cause 50% of Fortune 500 companies and executives to disappear, moving five times faster than the internet age. He predicts rapid job destruction, especially for entry-level roles, necessitating urgent re-education. Only adaptable companies that reinvent themselves will survive this unprecedented business climate.
title: Former Cisco CEO's dangerous prediction goes beyond AI replacing human jobs

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: US researchers successfully created early-stage human embryos from adult skin cells, bypassing traditional egg cells through advanced DNA manipulation. This groundbreaking OHSU study, mirroring cloning techniques, generated functional eggs that developed into early embryos. The innovation offers significant hope for infertility and same-sex couples, despite current low success rates and ethical considerations requiring further refinement.
title: Scientists turn human skin cells into eggs in groundbreaking fertility breakthrough

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Women's World Cup winner Divya Deshmukh lightened the mood with a jersey typo during the 'Checkmate: USA vs India' exhibition. However, Team India suffered a 5-0 defeat to Team USA, highlighted by Hikaru Nakamura's dramatic bullet win over Gukesh Dommaraju. A return leg in India offers Team India a chance for redemption.
title: 'So sad!': Divya Deshmukh reacts to hilarious typo on her jersey - Watch

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Defying a US government shutdown, the stock market surged to record highs, with broad gains across indices and assets. While AI optimism and anticipated Fed rate cuts fuel the rally, experts caution about expensive valuations nearing dot-com bubble levels. Future performance hinges on corporate earnings and AI's ability to boost productivity.
title: Wall Street rallying despite gov shutdown concerns, here is what to look for

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former India selector Krishnamachari Srikkanth slammed Harshit Rana's ODI squad inclusion for the Australia tour, questioning constant reshuffles and Sanju Samson's omission. Srikkanth criticized Rana's rapid rise, unimpressive Asia Cup showing, and "filmy gimmicks," suggesting such selections jeopardize India's 2027 World Cup ambitions and dent player confidence.
title: 'Why is he even in the team?' – Ex-India captain lambasts Harshit selection

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Cardiologist Dmitry Yaranov highlights amyloidosis as an underdiagnosed cause of heart failure, often mistaken for hypertension or aging. This condition involves misfolded proteins stiffening the heart, making it difficult to pump blood effectively. Symptoms mimic common heart issues, leading to years of misdiagnosis, yet early detection is vital for patient outcomes.
title: Cardiologist reveals surprising cause of heart failure; not high BP or clogged arteries

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former Pakistan cricketer Danish Kaneria denied seeking Indian citizenship, stating he lives in the USA with his family. He expressed pride in his Pakistani identity despite facing discrimination and conversion pressure, clarifying his positive comments about India are not for citizenship. Kaneria, who calls India his ancestral land, also mentioned the CAA and his commitment to exposing anti-nationals.
title: 'Pakistan my Janmabhoomi, but India is my Matrubhumi': Ex-Pak cricketer

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Shata Dhauta Ghrita, an ancient Ayurvedic remedy is considered the perfect remedy for a healthy, soft and glowing skin. This ghee is washed 100 times with water in a copper vessel till it turns creamy and light.  Traditionally used for soothing burns, skin issues, and anti-aging, this natural preparation offers a rediscovered holistic, chemical-free alternative for modern skin rejuvenation.
title: Shata Dhauta Ghrita: Why it is the ultimate Indian beauty secret for soft, bright skin

author: SAURABH SINHA
title: UK: Air India Dreamliner RAM deploys in final approach; lands safely, grounded for checks

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Kalimpong faced multiple landslides on Saturday after continuous heavy rainfall, disrupting traffic on NH10 and NH717A. Authorities confirmed no major damage or casualties, with teams actively clearing debris to restore connectivity. Heavy rain is predicted for West Bengal until October 6 due to a Bay of Bengal depression, urging vigilance.
title: West Bengal rains: Several dead as landslides hit Darjeeling district

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma questioned the "poisoning" claims in Zubeen Garg's mysterious death, urging patience for the viscera report and cooperation from Singapore witnesses. He highlighted that the allegation came from an accused, not authorities. A judicial commission has been formed, and four individuals, including the alleged poisoners and the accuser, have been arrested in the ongoing probe.
title: Zubeen Garg death mystery continues: Assam CM questions bandmate's 'poisoning' claim

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Greta Thunberg reported harsh treatment, dehydration, and bedbug-induced rashes in Israeli custody after her detention from a Gaza aid flotilla. Other activists alleged she was forced to hold Israeli flags, while NGOs cited systematic rights violations for detainees. Israel's embassy, however, denied all allegations, stating proper care was provided.
title: 'Did unimaginable things': Greta Thunberg accuses Israel of harsh treatment in detention

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: Marine biologists identified a new deep-sea coral species, Iridogorgia chewbacca. This coral was found near Molokaʻi and the Mariana Trench. Its long, shaggy branches resemble Chewbacca's fur. It thrives 400 to 1,000 metres deep. This discovery expands marine life knowledge and highlights deep-sea conservation needs.
title: Iridogorgia chewbacca: The deep-sea Wookiee coral found 400–1000m below

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: Kayla Nicole, Travis Kelce's ex-girlfriend, posted messages on social media. This followed speculation about Taylor Swift's song 'Opalite'. Fans believe Swift's lyrics from 'The Life of a Showgirl' targeted Nicole. Nicole shared photos and a video clip. Her posts are interpreted as a response to the alleged diss track. The situation adds to ongoing discussions about the celebrities.
title: Kayla Nicole fires back at Taylor Swift after alleged diss in ‘Opalite’ track

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India's T20I captain Suryakumar Yadav expressed his regret at never playing under MS Dhoni's captaincy for the national team, though he admired his calm leadership. He described Virat Kohli as a hard taskmaster and Rohit Sharma as an inclusive leader.
title: Post Asia Cup win: Suryakumar Yadav reveals biggest regret; involves MS Dhoni

author: TNN
description: Mohammad Imran, a 32-year-old history-sheeter with over 50 previous cases, was arrested for disrupting Tis Hazari Court virtual hearings. He appeared on screen in his undergarments, smoking and drinking, using fake identities. Police tracked him down after a complex investigation, revealing his drug and alcohol addiction led him to crime.
title: Delhi court shocker: Man joins hearings in undergarments, smokes, drinks; arrested

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Rohit Sharma has been replaced by Shubman Gill as India's ODI captain for the upcoming Australia series, sparking debate over Rohit's future and his 2027 World Cup participation. Former coach Abhishek Nayar stressed the importance of clear communication in this transition, supporting Gill's leadership while highlighting Rohit's prior 2027 aspirations.
title: 'If you’re going to...' – Ex-India coach’s remark on Rohit’s removal

author: TNN
description: Kerala Police registered a case against a Tamil Nadu native for assaulting an Israeli tourist in Varkala. The tourist allegedly snatched the man's mobile phone and threw it into the Arabian Sea, leading to the assault.
title: Kerala: TN man slaps Israeli tourist in Varkala after mobile snatching incident; booked

author: AMARJEET SINGH
description: A doctor in Chhindwara, Madhya Pradesh, has been arrested after 11 children reportedly died from consuming contaminated Coldrif cough syrup. Dr. Praveen Soni prescribed the syrup, with most children treated at his clinic. Police have also booked the Tamil Nadu-based pharmaceutical company responsible for manufacturing the alleged contaminated medicine.
title: MP cough syrup deaths: Doctor held after 11 kids die from toxic Coldrif; TN manufacturers booked

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Hamas's readiness to release hostages under US President Donald Trump’s ceasefire plan has sparked guarded optimism from Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, who vows to disarm the group. Mediated talks are set for Egypt, aiming for a deal involving hostage-prisoner exchanges and Israeli withdrawal. Despite hopes for peace, violence persists in Gaza, and questions remain about the plan's full implementation.
title: All eyes on Gaza: Netanyahu positive on Hamas deal, Trump wary of any 'delay'

author: TNN
description: Severe cyclonic storm Shakhti, formed off the Gujarat coast, moved westwards on Saturday, projected to curve east-northeastwards and weaken by October 6, 2025. Fishermen are advised against venturing into the northwest Arabian Sea. Concurrently, parts of Gujarat, including Dwarka and Ambaji, experienced rainfall, with Ahmedabad expecting light showers.
title: 'Cyclone Shakhti': IMD issues warning for Maha, Guj fishermen; heavy rain expected on Oct 8-9

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump authorized 300 National Guard troops to Chicago to protect federal officers and assets, citing "lawlessness" and a recent shooting incident involving a federal officer and an armed motorist. This move is part of his broader anti-crime operations in Democratic-run cities, though a similar deployment to Portland was recently blocked by a federal judge.
title: 'Lawlessness plaguing US': Trump authorises 300 National Guard troops to Chicago

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: The BCCI announced Shubman Gill as the new ODI captain, concluding Rohit Sharma's successful leadership. Former cricketer Mohammad Kaif criticized this decision, highlighting Rohit's impressive record, including two recent ICC trophy wins, and questioning the premature transition. Rohit's future in ODI cricket and the 2027 World Cup now remain uncertain.
title: 'Rohit gave India 16 yrs, but we couldn't': Gill's role sparks questions

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Shubman Gill has been appointed India's new ODI captain for the upcoming Australia tour, replacing Rohit Sharma, with Shreyas Iyer named vice-captain. This leadership transition is seen as a forward-looking move for the 2027 World Cup, as Rohit Sharma steps away from all leadership roles. Experts praise Gill's appointment as crucial for shaping Indian cricket's future.
title: 'I don't see Virat, Rohit playing 2027 ODI World Cup'

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India secured an emphatic innings-and-140-run victory over West Indies, extending their unbeaten home streak. Jasprit Bumrah's viral Instagram post, "bayki sab fake hai," celebrated Mohammed Siraj's stellar 4-40 spell, referencing an old meme. Ravindra Jadeja, KL Rahul, and Dhruv Jurel also shone in the dominant win, with the second Test scheduled for October 10.
title: IND vs WI: Bumrah's social media post after 1st test win goes viral

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Kantara Chapter 1 has emerged as a box office phenomenon, grossing an impressive Rs 162.85 crore net in India over its initial three days. The Rishab Shetty-led prequel shattered records, becoming the highest-grossing Kannada film of the year and surpassing major Indian releases. With significant overseas earnings, the film is proving to be a massive commercial success, captivating audiences globally.
title: Kantara Chapter 1 box office day 3: Rishab Shetty's film earns over Rs 160 cr

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Bruins' new forward Mark Kastelic charged Rangers' Matt Rempe in their final preseason game after both left the penalty box. This incident followed earlier physical plays and penalties, showcasing Kastelic's gritty character despite a significant size disadvantage. The fight, deemed a draw, highlighted Kastelic's readiness for tough bottom-six roles ahead of the Bruins' October 2025 season opener.
title: Mark Kastelic charges at Rangers’ 6'9" Matt Rempe, refuses to flinch

author: SEHJAL GUPTA
description: Former NFL quarterback and FOX Sports analyst Mark Sanchez was stabbed in Indianapolis early Saturday, October 4, 2025. Hospitalized with stab wounds, Sanchez, 38, was subsequently arrested, facing three misdemeanor charges including battery and public intoxication. Police confirmed it was an isolated disturbance, not a random attack, while Sanchez remains in stable condition.
title: Mark Sanchez arrested after stabbing in Indianapolis as police reveal charges

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Aspirin's role in preventing colorectal cancer is nuanced. While high-risk individuals, including those with unhealthy lifestyles or Lynch syndrome, may significantly benefit, its use carries risks like bleeding. Recent guidelines urge caution, advising against routine use for many due to potential harms and unclear benefits for the general population.
title: Should you take aspirin for colon or rectal cancer? Dos and don’ts explained

author: CH SUSHIL RAO
description: A 28-year-old Hyderabad student, Pole Chandrasekhar, was fatally shot in Texas, US, on October 3 during a suspected armed robbery at his part-time gas station job. Chandrasekhar, who was pursuing a master's, died on the spot. Telangana Chief Minister Revanth Reddy expressed condolences and assured government support to repatriate his remains, with coordination underway with Indian officials.
title: 'Went to build better future': How 'robbery attempt' claimed Indian student's life in US

author: NIKHIL SHARMA
description: A 29-year-old foreign languages teacher in Gurgaon has accused four gym trainers of sexual assault and gang rape. The victim met one suspect, Gaurav, at a party, later agreeing to meet him on October 1. At a friend's address, Gaurav allegedly assaulted her, then called three others who also raped her. Police arrested all four suspects, now in judicial custody.
title: Gurgaon horror: Invited by friend for party, teacher gang-raped by 4 men; all arrested

author: TNN
description: The Statistics Ministry has sought views on including free PDS items in the Consumer Price Index compilation, a crucial step during its ongoing revision. This update aims to strengthen the CPI by revising item weights and the consumption basket, with a new base year of 2024. The decision could significantly impact headline inflation and monetary policy.
title: Government seeks views on including PDS food grains in CPI series

author: SAHIL MALHOTRA
description: The Indian team management and the BCCI seems to be convinced that Rohit Sharma will not last till the 2027 ODI World Cup but the situation, surprisingly, has come down to a point where both Rohit and Virat Kohli, born two years apart and having different fitness levels, are being looked at from the same longevity lens.
title: IND vs AUS: New skipper! Inside story of Gill's elevation as ODI captain

author: PATHIKRIT CHAKRABORTY
title: Love story that began with awrong number ended in murder

author: PRADEEP GUPTA
description: Bhiwandi police arrested a 58-year-old US national and two local residents for allegedly attempting to convert villagers to Christianity in Chimbipada. The accused, including James Watson on a business visa, reportedly preached during a prayer meet, claiming Hinduism was superstitious and offering miraculous cures. They face charges under new laws and the Foreigners Act for misusing the visa.
title: Maharashtra: US national among 3 held for illegal conversion bid in Bhiwandi

author: MAHIMA ROY
description: Taylor Swift's new album, "The Life of a Showgirl," has ignited fan speculation that a track, "Cancelled," targets Brittany Mahomes. This drama resurfaced Mahomes' past work with Kim Kardashian, fueling rumors of a fallout. However, Swift clarified the song addresses her personal experiences with public judgment and scandalous moments, not a specific individual, despite earlier sightings of the two together.
title: Taylor Swift fans think she called out Brittany Mahomes over Kim Kardashian's past
